:::.col-12 .col-md-5
### What is Latitude?

* **Definition:** Latitude provides horizontal axis by carving the globe into parallel rings.It gives the `↑↓ vertical jump` to reach a point vertically in a map.
* **Parallels of Latitude:** There are 180° parallels of latitude.Starting from 0 to 90 top(North) and 0 to -90(South).So total 180 vertical jump line.Each line is called parallel.
* Each parallel forms a complete **circle**.
* The distance between any two parallels of latitude is **always equal**.But parallels are **not of equal length**.The equator has the maximum length.
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-7
![img](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Nh-em0n/QDoc/main/BCS/Geography/05.1.The%20Universe%20and%20Our%20Earth/resources/latitude-dgrm1.png)
:::
:::


