:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-6
**Key Reference Points:**

* **The Equator ($0^\circ$):** The most important latitude and the largest circle (known as the *great circle*). It divides the earth into the Northern Hemisphere and the Southern Hemisphere.
* **The North Pole ($90^\circ\text{ N}$) and South Pole ($90^\circ\text{ S}$):** Fixed points that serve as the basic points of reference.
:::
